   478 				        ; Keep the keyboard scan healthy on real hardware. In 16-BIT mode AUDCTL=$78
   479 				        ; clocks POKEY's serial logic, which latches stale serial-status bits and wedges
   480 				        ; the keyboard debounce after a few frames — without this, 16-BIT mode stops
   481 				        ; responding to the keyboard. Clear the status latches and re-assert the scan
   482 				        ; config every frame: cheap, idempotent, and harmless (bit1 stays high, so the
   483 				        ; live key is never dropped). REQUIRED for 16-BIT — verified on real hardware.
   484 218A 8D 0A D2		        sta SKRES               ; (any write) clear stale serial/keyboard status latches
   485 218D A9 03		        lda #$03
   486 218F 8D 0F D2		        sta SKCTL               ; keyboard scan + debounce, serial off
