  1108 				;  Drum voice: a noise-percussion hit on channel 4 (its own subsystem, not the
  1109 				;  ADSR voice engine). Triggered by a $FD sequencer step. DRUM param = decay
  1110 				;  length (0 = off). 8-bit clock modes only (in 16-bit, channel 4 is a joined
  1111 				;  high channel). drum_tick runs after update_sound and overrides channel 4
  1112 				;  while a hit rings; when it ends, voice 3's normal output resumes.
  1113 				; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
